al and imaginative experience and accords the philosopher an exceptional dignity and freedom. With reference to both Islamic and Western philosophers, Azadpur discusses how Islamic Peripatetic thought can provide an antidote to some of modernity's philosophical problems. A discussion of the development of later Islamic Peripatetic thought is also included.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aIslamic philosophy. 0aPhilosophy. 4aArea Studies : Middle East Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Comparative Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Islam. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438437644423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438437644/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles